==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[lux]]'', "light-bearer".

===Noun===
'''Lucifer'''

#{{proper noun}} A name or title of [[Satan]], referring to him before his fall into sin.
#{{proper noun}} The [[planet]] [[Venus]] as the [[daystar]].

